{
  "answer": "**Charles Comte does this in *Traité de Législation: VOL III*, chapter 48 (\"De la supériorité des peuples d’espèce caucasienne sur les peuples des autres espèces. — Des causes\").**[^1]\n\nHe notes that Roman slaves produced Epictetus, Phaedrus, and Terence, then rhetorically asks what geniuses the Negro slaves of Jamaica or Saint Lucia have produced. He replies that demanding Terence-level comedies from black slaves cutting sugar cane commits the same fallacy as \"concluding that the citizens of the United States are a degenerate race, for the reason that they have produced no orator like Cicero, or no poet like Virgil.\"[^1]\n\n[^1]: Charles Comte, *Traité de Législation: VOL III*, [paragraph](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-iii-ca589a/48-de-la-superiorite-des-peuples-d-espece-caucasienne/translation/#p-81116a).",
